#Detection of Outliers and Cleaning the Dataset

detect_outliers <- function(x) {
  Q1 <- quantile(x, 0.25)
  Q3 <- quantile(x, 0.75)
  IQR <- Q3 - Q1
  lower_bound <- Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
  upper_bound <- Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
  outliers <- x[x < lower_bound | x > upper_bound]
  return(outliers)
}

air_time_outliers <- detect_outliers(flight_data$AIR_TIME)
arrival_delay_outliers <- detect_outliers(flight_data$ARRIVAL_DELAY)
departure_delay_outliers <- detect_outliers(flight_data$DEPARTURE_DELAY)
elapsed_time_outliers <- detect_outliers(flight_data$ELAPSED_TIME)
scheduled_time_outliers <- detect_outliers(flight_data$SCHEDULED_TIME)

#Identify the indices of the rows to keep
keep_indices <- !((flight_data$AIR_TIME %in% air_time_outliers) | (flight_data$ARRIVAL_DELAY %in% arrival_delay_outliers) | (flight_data$DEPARTURE_DELAY %in% departure_delay_outliers) | (flight_data$ELAPSED_TIME %in% elapsed_time_outliers) | (flight_data$SCHEDULED_TIME %in% scheduled_time_outliers))

#Subset the data to only keep rows without outliers
flight_data_clean <- flight_data[keep_indices, ]

set.seed(1234)

flight_data_mixed<-flights_modified_final[order(runif(4682)),]
flight_data_training<-flight_data_mixed[1:3278,]
flight_data_testing<-flight_data_mixed[3279:4682,]
#Build a Full Model
flight_data_full<-lm(DISTANCE~.,data=flight_data_training)
summary(flight_data_full)

#-1<= r <= 1
#r      dw
#-1      4
#0       2
#1       0
#If residuals are not correlated, we get dw very close to 2 (1.99, not 1.9)

#2 - 4, the residuals are negatively autocorrelated

#Split the data into training and validation sets
set.seed(567)
part<-sample(2, nrow(X), replace=TRUE, prob=c(0.7,0.3))
X_train<-X[part==1, ] #Training Data
X_test<-X[part==2, ] #Testing Data
Y_train<-Y[part==1] #Training Data
Y_test<-Y[part==2] #Testing Data
#Perform Ridge Regression
ridge_reg<-glmnet(X_train, Y_train, alpha=0, lambda=lambda)
summary(ridge_reg)
##           Length Class     Mode   
## a0         100   -none-    numeric
## beta      1900   dgCMatrix S4     
## df         100   -none-    numeric
## dim          2   -none-    numeric
## lambda     100   -none-    numeric
## dev.ratio  100   -none-    numeric
## nulldev      1   -none-    numeric
## npasses      1   -none-    numeric
## jerr         1   -none-    numeric
## offset       1   -none-    logical
## call         5   -none-    call   
## nobs         1   -none-    numeric
#Find the best lambda via cross-validation
ridge_reg1<-cv.glmnet(X_train, Y_train, alpha=0)
bestlam<-ridge_reg1$lambda.min
print(bestlam)
## [1] 45.34839
#Predict on the validation set
ridge.pred<-predict(ridge_reg, s=bestlam, newx=X_test)

#Calculate the mean squared error
mse<-mean((Y_test - ridge.pred)^2)
print(paste("Mean Squared Error: ",mse))
## [1] "Mean Squared Error:  6964.30325085558"
#Calculate R squared Value
sst<-sum((Y_test - mean(Y_test))^2)
sse<-sum((Y_test - ridge.pred)^2)
r2<- 1 - (sse/sst)
print(paste("R square: ",r2))
## [1] "R square:  0.968033654288453"
#Perform Lasso Regression
lasso_reg<-glmnet(X_train, Y_train, alpha=1, lambda=lambda)
summary(lasso_reg)

## [1] 0.8902074
#Predict on the validation set

#Calculate the mean squared error

print(paste("Mean Squared Error: ",mse))
## [1] "Mean Squared Error:  6505.80165203727"
